# Lumina Audit Trail Patterns

## HasAuditTrail Trait

Add the `HasAuditTrail` trait to any model that should track changes:

```php
<?php

namespace App\Models;

use Illuminate\Database\Eloquent\Factories\HasFactory;
use Illuminate\Database\Eloquent\SoftDeletes;
use Lumina\LaravelApi\Traits\HasValidation;
use Lumina\LaravelApi\Traits\HidableColumns;
use Lumina\LaravelApi\Traits\HasAuditTrail;

class Article extends \Illuminate\Database\Eloquent\Model
{
    use HasFactory;
    use SoftDeletes;
    use HasValidation;
    use HidableColumns;
    use HasAuditTrail;

    protected $fillable = [
        'title',
        'body',
        'status',
    ];
}
```

## Tracked Events

The `HasAuditTrail` trait automatically records the following events:

| Event           | Trigger                                 |
|-----------------|-----------------------------------------|
| `created`       | A new record is created                 |
| `updated`       | An existing record is modified          |
| `deleted`       | A record is soft-deleted                |
| `force_deleted` | A record is permanently deleted         |
| `restored`      | A soft-deleted record is restored       |

## Excluding Fields from Audit

By default, `password` and `remember_token` are excluded from audit logs. Customize this with the `$auditExclude` property:

```php
class User extends \Illuminate\Database\Eloquent\Model
{
    use HasFactory;
    use SoftDeletes;
    use HasValidation;
    use HidableColumns;
    use HasAuditTrail;

    // These fields will NOT be recorded in audit logs
    protected $auditExclude = [
        'password',
        'remember_token',
        'two_factor_secret',
        'api_token',
    ];
}
```

## AuditLog Model Fields

Each audit log entry contains:

| Field         | Type      | Description                                    |
|---------------|-----------|------------------------------------------------|
| `id`          | bigint    | Primary key                                    |
| `auditable_type` | string | Polymorphic model class (e.g., `App\Models\Article`) |
| `auditable_id`   | bigint | ID of the audited record                       |
| `event`       | string    | Event name (created, updated, deleted, etc.)   |
| `old_values`  | json      | Previous values (null for `created` events)    |
| `new_values`  | json      | New values (null for `deleted` events)         |
| `user_id`     | bigint    | ID of the user who performed the action        |
| `created_at`  | timestamp | When the audit entry was recorded              |
| `updated_at`  | timestamp | When the audit entry was last modified         |

## Polymorphic Relationship

Access audit logs through the model's `auditLogs()` relationship:

```php
$article = Article::find(1);

// Get all audit logs for this article
$logs = $article->auditLogs()->latest()->get();

// Get only update events
$updates = $article->auditLogs()->where('event', 'updated')->get();

// Access old and new values
foreach ($logs as $log) {
    echo $log->event;         // "updated"
    echo $log->old_values;    // {"status": "draft"}
    echo $log->new_values;    // {"status": "published"}
    echo $log->user_id;       // 42
    echo $log->created_at;    // 2025-01-15 10:30:00
}
```

## API Endpoint for Fetching Logs

Lumina automatically exposes an API endpoint to fetch audit logs for any auditable model:

```
GET /api/{org}/articles/{id}/audit-logs
```

Response format:

```json
{
    "data": [
        {
            "id": 1,
            "event": "created",
            "old_values": null,
            "new_values": {
                "title": "My First Article",
                "body": "Hello world",
                "status": "draft"
            },
            "user_id": 42,
            "created_at": "2025-01-15T10:00:00.000000Z"
        },
        {
            "id": 2,
            "event": "updated",
            "old_values": {
                "status": "draft"
            },
            "new_values": {
                "status": "published"
            },
            "user_id": 42,
            "created_at": "2025-01-15T10:30:00.000000Z"
        }
    ],
    "pagination": {
        "current_page": 1,
        "per_page": 15,
        "total": 2
    }
}
```

## Complete Example

```php
<?php

namespace App\Models;

use Illuminate\Database\Eloquent\Factories\HasFactory;
use Illuminate\Database\Eloquent\SoftDeletes;
use Lumina\LaravelApi\Traits\HasValidation;
use Lumina\LaravelApi\Traits\HidableColumns;
use Lumina\LaravelApi\Traits\BelongsToOrganization;
use Lumina\LaravelApi\Traits\HasAuditTrail;

class Invoice extends \Illuminate\Database\Eloquent\Model
{
    use HasFactory;
    use SoftDeletes;
    use HasValidation;
    use HidableColumns;
    use BelongsToOrganization;
    use HasAuditTrail;

    protected $fillable = [
        'invoice_number',
        'amount',
        'status',
        'due_date',
        'organization_id',
    ];

    // Exclude sensitive financial metadata from audit logs
    protected $auditExclude = [
        'stripe_payment_intent_id',
        'internal_processing_notes',
    ];

    protected $validationRules = [
        'invoice_number' => 'required|string|unique:invoices,invoice_number',
        'amount' => 'required|numeric|min:0',
        'status' => 'required|in:draft,sent,paid,overdue,cancelled',
        'due_date' => 'required|date|after:today',
    ];
}
```

## DON'Ts

- **DO NOT** include sensitive fields like passwords, tokens, or secrets in audit logs. Always add them to `$auditExclude`.
- **DO NOT** rely on audit logs for business logic or authorization decisions. Audit logs are for historical record-keeping only.
- **DO NOT** modify audit log entries after creation. They are intended to be an immutable historical record.
